commits.commitMessage:
HTTPS connection failed if server certificate contains SAN

Description:
HTTPS connection failed if a subjectAltName extension of
type dNSName is present and the server name doesn't match
with DNSname (*.pipedream.net and *.pipedream.com)

Root Cause:
In establishing a TLS connection.
In step3: server certificate (server -> client)
If a subjectAltName extension of
type dNSName is present in the certificate,
it SHOULD be used as the source of the server's identity.

Solution:
If the server certificate has SAN extenstions, we will add it to hostname.

Resolves: LE-16532
Related: MOLRC9X07-315
Change-Id: Icc0056995a3559dc5a82e5f49c3fe2ef0ead54ad
commits.subject: HTTPS connection failed if server certificate contains SAN
